  "text": "Considering the centre of panel vacuum insulation core thermal conductivity of 4.11 mWm -1 K -1 , the U -value at centre of panel of CIP was theoretically expected to be around 0.20 Wm -2 K -1 . However, small size of VIPs used in this study and edge effect due to the individual panel and air gap between two VIPs led to a negative effect on the U-value of panel and a higher U-value of 0.38 Wm -2 K -1 was obtained in this investigation. The increase in thermal conductivity for small vacuum insulation panel can easily be between 11% and 15% higher than the centre of panel thermal conductivity [CITATION_1] . Edge effect due to air gap between small VIPs can also reduce the thermal resistance and the practical equivalent thermal conductivity value was measured to be about 8 mWm -1 K -1 for panel size 300 mm × 300mm (Lorenzati, Fantucci, Capozzoli, Perino, 2015) .",
